abstract:
Disordered spring networks are a well-established model system to study fracture in a wide range of materials, from ceramics to polymer networks and mechanical metamaterials, across length scales from the atomistic to the macroscopic. A central quantity characterizing fracture is the apparent fracture energy $G^c$, which measures the resistance to the propagation of a preexisting dominant crack. While it is well established that disorder can increase $G^c$ through crack arrest by local inhomogeneities, its dependence on the degree of disorder remains poorly understood. Here, we study the effect of varying concentrations of missing bonds on crack propagation of an otherwise perfect two-dimensional triangular network of springs. For a given network with a fixed concentration of missing bonds, the apparent fracture energy $G^c(a)$ increases with crack advance $a$. This behavior can be explained by mapping the effect of the missing bonds onto an equivalent local fracture energy landscape $\Gamma^{loc}(a)$ and applying established theories linking planar crack arrest with fluctuations in $\Gamma^{loc}(a)$. For increasing fraction of missing bonds $
u$, the standard deviation of the fluctuations of $\Gamma^{loc}$ increases with $\sqrt{
u}$, which we explain by considering a random-walk-like superposition of perturbations caused by individual missing bonds. We demonstrate that as a consequence of crack arrest by fluctuations in $\Gamma^{loc}$, the average $G^c(a)$ follows the same $\sqrt{
u}$ scaling. Furthermore, we observe that the probability density of $\Gamma^{loc}$ has an exponential tail leading to a logarithmic increase of $G^c(a)$ with crack advance $a$. Our results quantitatively link microstructural disorder to macroscopic fracture energy and paves the way for quantitative predictions of the fracture energy in a wide variety of materials.

summary:
无序弹簧网络是一个完善的模型系统，用于研究从陶瓷到聚合物网络和机械超材料的各种材料的断裂，涵盖从原子到宏观的长度尺度。表征断裂的一个中心量是表观断裂能 $G^c$，它测量对预先存在的主要裂纹扩展的阻力。虽然众所周知，无序可以通过局部不均匀性止裂来增加 $G^c$，但它对无序程度的依赖性仍然知之甚少。在这里，我们研究了不同浓度的缺失键对完美的二维三角形弹簧网络的裂纹扩展的影响。对于缺失键固定浓度的给定网络，表观断裂能 $G^c(a)$ 随着裂纹推进 $a$ 增加。这种行为可以通过将缺失键的影响映射到等效的局部断裂能景观 $\Gamma^{loc}(a)$ 上并应用将平面止裂与 $\Gamma^{loc}(a)$ 波动联系起来的既定理论来解释。

对于缺失键 $
u$ 比例的增加，$\Gamma^{loc}$ 波动的标准差随着 $\sqrt{
u}$ 的增加而增加，我们通过考虑由单个缺失键引起的扰动的随机游走叠加来解释这一点。我们证明，由于 $\Gamma^{loc}$ 波动导致裂纹停止，平均 $G^c(a)$ 遵循相同的 $\sqrt{
u}$ 缩放比例。此外，我们观察到 $\Gamma^{loc}$ 的概率密度具有指数尾部，导致 $G^c(a)$ 随着裂纹提前 $a$ 以对数增加。我们的结果定量地将微观结构紊乱与宏观断裂能联系起来，并为定量预测各种材料的断裂能铺平了道路。
